    <p>BANGKOK • Thai­land’s new army chief pledged yesterday to fol­low his pre­de­ces­sor, who has taken a hard line against anti-govern­ment groups, and em­pha­sised the importance of pro­tect­ing the monar­chy.</p>
    <p>The ap­point­ment of Gen­eral Narong­pan Jit­tkaew­tae in an an­nual mil­i­tary reshuf­fle comes as Thai­land’s army- and palace-dom­i­nated es­tab­lish­ment is deal­ing with more than two months of anti-govern­ment protests.</p>


